{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F939ESVU5rRbU2dAubhzbM","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"use client\";\n2\t\n3\timport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\n4\timport Chip from \"@mui/material/Chip\";\n5\timport Popover from \"@mui/material/Popover\";\n6\timport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n7\timport { useState } from \"react\";\n8\t\n9\tinterface JsonChipProps {\n10\t  properties: string;\n11\t}\n12\t\n13\texport function JsonChip({ properties }: JsonChipProps): React.JSX.Element {\n14\t  const [anchorEl, setAnchorEl] = useState<HTMLElement | null>(null);\n15\t\n16\t  let parsed: Record<string, unknown> = {};\n17\t  try {\n18\t    if (properties && properties.trim() !== \"\") {\n19\t      parsed = JSON.parse(properties) as Record<string, unknown>;\n20\t    }\n21\t  } catch {\n22\t    parsed = {};\n23\t  }\n24\t\n25\t  const keys = Object.keys(parsed);\n26\t\n27\t  if (keys.length === 0) {\n28\t    return <Chip label=\"No properties\" size=\"small\" variant=\"outlined\" />;\n29\t  }\n30\t\n31\t  const preview = keys.slice(0, 2).join(\", \") + (keys.length > 2 ? \", …\" : \"\");\n32\t\n33\t  return (\n34\t    <>\n35\t      <Chip\n36\t        label={preview}\n37\t        size=\"small\"\n38\t        variant=\"outlined\"\n39\t        onClick={(e: React.MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) =>\n40\t          setAnchorEl(e.currentTarget)\n41\t        }\n42\t        sx={{ cursor: \"pointer\" }}\n43\t        aria-label=\"Show properties\"\n44\t      />\n45\t      <Popover\n46\t        open={Boolean(anchorEl)}\n47\t        anchorEl={anchorEl}\n48\t        onClose={() => setAnchorEl(null)}\n49\t        anchorOrigin={{ vertical: \"bottom\", horizontal: \"left\" }}\n50\t      >\n51\t        <Box sx={{ p: 2 }}>\n52\t          <Typography\n53\t            component=\"pre\"\n54\t            variant=\"body2\"\n55\t            sx={{ fontFamily: \"monospace\", whiteSpace: \"pre-wrap\", m: 0 }}\n56\t          >\n57\t            {JSON.stringify(parsed, null, 2)}\n58\t          </Typography>\n59\t        </Box>\n60\t      </Popover>\n61\t    </>\n62\t  );\n63\t}\n64\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"210aa803-a4e1-4c9d-860c-765ebdce1d01","uuid":"91c7b6ba-766a-491d-961d-4dd3a4211165","timestamp":"2026-04-15T17:37:54.972Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/ui/JsonChip.tsx","content":"\"use client\";\n\nimport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\nimport Chip from \"@mui/material/Chip\";\nimport Popover from \"@mui/material/Popover\";\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\nimport { useState } from \"react\";\n\ninterface JsonChipProps {\n  properties: string;\n}\n\nexport function JsonChip({ properties }: JsonChipProps): React.JSX.Element {\n  const [anchorEl, setAnchorEl] = useState<HTMLElement | null>(null);\n\n  let parsed: Record<string, unknown> = {};\n  try {\n    if (properties && properties.trim() !== \"\") {\n      parsed = JSON.parse(properties) as Record<string, unknown>;\n    }\n  } catch {\n    parsed = {};\n  }\n\n  const keys = Object.keys(parsed);\n\n  if (keys.length === 0) {\n    return <Chip label=\"No properties\" size=\"small\" variant=\"outlined\" />;\n  }\n\n  const preview = keys.slice(0, 2).join(\", \") + (keys.length > 2 ? \", …\" : \"\");\n\n  return (\n    <>\n      <Chip\n        label={preview}\n        size=\"small\"\n        variant=\"outlined\"\n        onClick={(e: React.MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) =>\n          setAnchorEl(e.currentTarget)\n        }\n        sx={{ cursor: \"pointer\" }}\n        aria-label=\"Show properties\"\n      />\n      <Popover\n        open={Boolean(anchorEl)}\n        anchorEl={anchorEl}\n        onClose={() => setAnchorEl(null)}\n        anchorOrigin={{ vertical: \"bottom\", horizontal: \"left\" }}\n      >\n        <Box sx={{ p: 2 }}>\n          <Typography\n            component=\"pre\"\n            variant=\"body2\"\n            sx={{ fontFamily: \"monospace\", whiteSpace: \"pre-wrap\", m: 0 }}\n          >\n            {JSON.stringify(parsed, null, 2)}\n          </Typography>\n        </Box>\n      </Popover>\n    </>\n  );\n}\n","numLines":64,"startLine":1,"totalLines":64}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014Czya1gWaah4N42G17Zqjs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, `JsonChip` has `\"use client\"` and uses `useState`. So `UserTimeline` uses `JsonChip` which is a client component. `UserTimeline` itself has `\"use client\"` which is correct since it imports a client component.\n\nNow, the key question: can a Server Component (page.tsx) render `UserTimeline` (which is a Client Component with `\"use client\"`)?\n\nYES! Server Components can render Client Components. The Client Component's SSR HTML will still be included in the initial response. The `\"use client\"` boundary means that component and its subtree will be hydrated on the client.\n \nNow I'm planning the refactored page structure: `page.tsx` stays as a Server Component, calls `getUserProfile` server-side, and renders `UserTimeline` as a Client Component that still gets SSR'd. I'll make sure to always render the identity-cluster and user-timeline containers, showing user and device IDs when the profile exists or a fallback message otherwise, while wrapping the data fetch in error handling.\n\nI need to check how `params` works in Next.js 16 since it's now a Promise, and I should verify the Next.js version and available commands in the package.json.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2464,"cache_read_input_tokens":54911,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2464,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"210aa803-a4e1-4c9d-860c-765ebdce1d01","uuid":"20902f52-5d7d-42a2-a7b9-d0e36d13c783"}
