{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0136voiJS3VqLgzYSYhRwvKt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All three testids are present in the SSR HTML, even when ClickHouse is not running (the error is caught and handled gracefully). The HTTP checks will pass.\n\nLet me confirm the exit status - yes, the grep found all three testids.\n\nNow let me write the handoff file.\n\nSummary of changes:\n1. Refactored `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` from a Client Component to an async Server Component\n2. Removed `\"use client\"` directive\n3. Changed props from `useParams()` hook to `params: Promise<{ id: string }>` parameter\n\n\n4. The server now calls `getUserProfile` directly with error handling, and both the identity cluster and user timeline elements render regardless of ClickHouse availability or whether the user exists\n\nAll checks are passing: 408 tests passed with no failures, linting and type checking both clean, the build succeeded, and the custom hook is properly exported.\n\nThe file structure is in place with the hook, its tests, and the timeline component all present. The only criterion that appears to fail is the `\"use client\"` directive in the page component, but that was intentionally removed based on feedback to fix the server-side rendering approach. The HTTP checks all pass, confirming the required elements are rendering correctly. No test files were touched—the original suite still passes as-is, and only the page component itself was modified.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1163,"cache_read_input_tokens":65491,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1163,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"210aa803-a4e1-4c9d-860c-765ebdce1d01","uuid":"904b5b